page.title: 08ECOLOGY-NORTON LOW WOOD
page.content:
{Ecology}of Norton Low Wood. -------------------------------------- As I walked through Norton Low Wood on Saturday,7th.September 1985 I felt it must have remained the same throughout{generations}.The same air of peace,tranquility and timelessness offering refreshment to troubled minds.The{trees}are mainly Oak,Silver Birch and Rhododendron with a few Conifers,Rowans and Gorse. As I walked I heard the Stock Doves"Coo-coo"and a{bird},the little wren,looked up to enquire my reason for being there.There was the occasional raucous call of the pheasant,but in the main it was the stillness and quiet which prevailed.
--------------------------------------
